metadata.description:

metadata.name: Meander River Plot v2 #108
metadata.description: A calmer version of the meander algorithm. Just the loops of the line vectors with no influence from a noise field. I love watching these loop and swirl as I'm developing the piece - it's fun and relaxing.

metadata.name: String art generator #153
metadata.description:
Generative image with animation (1024x1024px) Vanilla JS

This project is a string-art simulator which weaves some patterns in different layouts to make beautiful compositions which can be played from the beginning.
The main features of this generative collection are the several Patterns and Layouts which combined make a huge amount of variations.

‚ÄúPattern‚Äù defined as the instructions that the thread has to follow to weave the result.
"Layout" defined as the setup of the nails on the board.

The thread is always continuous without interruptions.

Features:

Pattern (21)
Layout (10)
Palette (25)
Layout Mirror (None, Horizontal, Vertical)
ThreadType: (Silk, Wool)
ThreadThickness: (Regular, Thick)

Controls:

[P] Play. 
[R] Result.
[U] Undo. 
[N] Nails. Show/Hide the nails.

[S] Download snapshot (may be slow or unresponsive)

You can weave yourself
Click to change the thread color

This project is an homage to Mary Everest Boole who, more than 100 years ago, used string art to teach math to children.

metadata.name: Deep Forest #150
metadata.description:
I love being in nature and impressionistic paintings. Deep Forest is my latest attempt to combine them with JavaScript. The editions will range from open, sparse forests to lush, dense, leafy wonderlands. Fall editions may render as Klimpt-style birch forests - my original inspiration for this work.

Best viewed on a computer. It may take a few seconds to start drawing and, depending on complexity, several minutes to finish rendering. In live view, press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px.

Features:
- One of the four seasons
- Rare 10% night version with 50/50 for normal fireflies or "fire" fireflies. Night will only be spring or summer.
- Amount of atmosphere/haze
- Horizon line near the middle or 30% "high horizon" near the top
- Tint from one of 8 light and 7 shadow colors
- Strength of the light and shadow color tint
- Mixed tree trunks or 30% all birch
- 50/50 moss on tree trunks
- One of 8 flower colors in spring or summer
- One of 4 perspective transforms
- Straight, curved out, or 30% curved inward trunks
- 50/50 grass in fall or winter
- 85% will have flowers in spring and summer
- 95% will have underbrush
- 50/50 clouds or solid background
- 50/50 solid background will be vertical or swirls
- Ground hill height

metadata.name: Merkki #59
metadata.description:
Merkki is an exploration of primitive forms, randomness and bold lines.
Drawing inspiration from mid-70s iconic single-color logotypes, this project revolves heavily around constraints and minimalism.

- 5 different shape types
- 3 grid sizes
- Mostly monochrome, with occasional color accents

Press ‚Äús‚Äù to save a 4000x4000px image.

metadata.name: Postcards from Gaza #4
metadata.description:
A generative artwork that evokes devastation and suffering. The composition, created in 3D using a combinatory generation technique, depicts a pseudo-architectural structure ‚Äî or what remains of it ‚Äî emerging from a blood-red fog.
The piece is directly inspired by the ongoing tragedy in the Gaza Strip, reflecting on the devastating impact of armed conflicts on urban life, people, and the very essence of dwelling. "Postcards from Gaza" is not just an abstract artwork: it is a statement, a form of memory, and an act of protest, written in the language of generative art.

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #665
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Miniscapes #264
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: Acequia #308
metadata.description:
Acequia (‚Äúah-seh-kee-uh‚Äù) - a Spanish adaptation of the Arabic word as-sƒÅqiya, meaning ‚Äúwater carrier‚Äù. 

In our second collaboration, Rich and Rick are back with our blend of generative code, intricate design, attention to detail, and a splash of charm. 

‚Ä®Acequias are traditional irrigation canals used to distribute rainwater and snowmelt along a complex network of narrow channels. They are found in Spain, the American Southwest, and northern Mexico, where they are essential for sustaining fields, orchards, and gardens in semi-arid regions. ‚Ä®‚Ä®
Our aim in this series is to capture the essence of these waterways in bold geometric designs. Each piece is inspired by a mountain village or town in Andalusia (southern Spain). 

The location determines the cube designs and construction rules that are used to build the final output. These are combined with striking day/night palettes, outline styles, scales, climates, and a few surprises of course!


Controls (in live view): 

- Press [p] to pause water animation 
- Press [e] to complete water animation 
- Press [r] to reset water animation 
- Press [s] to save the current image 
- Press [h] for a high-res output suitable for printing 
- Press [b] to toggle the border
